ic minority children.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aBilingualism in childrenxUnited States. 0aBilingualism in childrenzUnited States. 0aKorean American childrenxLanguage. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aBilingual competence .  aBilingual development.  aBilingualism.  aChild language development.  aDual language development .  aEnglish.  aHeritage languages.  aKorean.  aLinguistic minority.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978185359748040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781853597480423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781853597480/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK